<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="branch-n">branch <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /brɑːntʃ/    美 /bræntʃ/  </p>
<p>[C]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>树枝；枝条：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>the bare branches of a tree in winter 
冬季光秃秃的树枝</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.<strong>分部；分支；支流；支脉：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>open / set up a branch office 
开分公司</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Today the organisation has branches in 90 countries in all five continents. 
今天该组织在五大洲的90个国家都设有分支机构。</p><footer>外研⑤ – 6</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>English is a branch of the Germanic family of languages. 
英语是日耳曼语系的一支。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a branch of the Rhine
莱茵河的支流</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>The head office of the bank is in Beijing, but it has <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (分部) all over the country.</li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. branches  </p></div>